So did Chisha mutter to himself, conscious of the role his much-younger friend had spoken of.

At that very moment, the Imperial Selection Ceremony, in which Vincent Abellux was to contend, would begin just half a year away.

△▼△▼△▼△

The death of former Emperor Drizen Vollachia and the subsequent start of the Imperial Selection Ceremony.

Because of his indisputable talents, Vincent Abellux was regarded as an enemy by his other siblings, and got caught into a web of concentrated attacks for a time.

However, as it turned out, Vincent lived up to his initial reputation and expectations, winning the Imperial Selection Ceremony with overwhelming strength.

Vincent Abellux, who had vanquished all his siblings and was adorned with the crown of blood of the Vollachian Empire ――No, the 77th Emperor Vincent Vollachia was born.

Part of that bloody path that Vincent walked and the great river of blood that Vincent trenched might be due in part to the contributions of Chisha and Cecilus, who served as his subordinates.

