During this battle, Chisha’s entrusted role was to make the very last move on the board――,

Chisha: [――I see that your younger sister has escaped unharmed. She may have quite the fierce and uninhibited personality, but I am sure she understands her predicament. I think things are settled, for the time being.]

It is in an office, namely a room in the Crystal Palace in Lupugana, the Imperial capital.

In that room used by the Emperor himself, the pinnacle of national politics, Chisha stepped into a situation where a familiar face was looking back at him, a situation that would take him a while to get comfortable with the dealings with a sense of calm.

The emperor himself, though, showed no sign of disturbing his usual manner when he sat on such an authoritative chair. Even when he was assured that his victory in the Imperial Selection Ceremony was unassailable, he did not show even a hint of a smile from a sense of accomplishment.

Vincent did not laugh, at least not while he was a prince or the Emperor.

At moments when he wasn't a prince, he would break character, crack a smile and even show a mischievous grin.

He became the Emperor. And he would not allow for a moment when the Emperor was not the Emperor.

――No, there was one shared moment where that was not the case.

Chisha: [I could not believe my ears when asked for a way to save Prisca-sama.]

Assuming that no one else was listening, Chisha spoke of the greatest secret of the Vollachian Empire, one in which he had participated.

Coinciding with the conclusion of the Imperial Election Ceremony, the birth of a new Emperor was announced.

But the fact of the matter was that the completion of the imperial succession had not been fulfilled in the ceremony in which the last of the imperial family would succeed to the throne. ――The last two remained.

The two were Vincent Abellux and Prisca Benedict.

Prisca Benedict was described as the tragic princess who gulped a cup of her own poison and lost her life.

In fact, she gulped down the poison but did not lose her life.

She gulped down this poison not from a cup, rather to save her squire, who was so concerned for her master that she clung to the possibility of saving her life.

The poison stopped Prisca's heart for a moment and ended it all before it started to beat again.

The Imperial Election Ceremony was over and Prisca Benedict was buried in a tomb.

Vincent Abellux became Emperor, and Prisca Benedict assumed a different identity, a life not by that name――.

Chisha: "If I were from a family that has served the Empire of old, I might have cautioned His Excellency that his wish was outrageous. However, I hail from a family of commoners."

There is no prestige, no tradition, and no basis for being particularly appreciative of them.

A certain amount of respect is given, value is acknowledged, but there is no mistaking that it is the best. In the Vollachian Empire, that is the way it is.

And that is why――,

Chisha: [I had not the slightest bit of hesitation in taking part in this plan.]

Vincent: [――――]

The Emperor's silence, Vincent's mind impossible to fathom, but his actions were clear.

Among his many siblings, Prisca was special to Vincent. Although Prisca shone brightly in Chisha's eyes because of her talent, it was not only her ability that made Vincent so interested in his younger sister, even though Vincent was much older than her.

Despite her arrogance, Prisca respected Vincent and treated him as a blood related elder brother.

The Imperial Election Ceremony is the fate of the royal family of Vollachia, thus preventing them from coexisting despite mutual recognition and compromise ――which was broken by Vincent's hand.

That was a small relief for Chisha and, more importantly, it was a relief.

Vincent's approach is to demonstrate his full capabilities within the position and role he has been given.

Vincent has not changed his way of thinking from the day they met to the present day, so what kind of rationality is manifested in the fact that he chose to let Prisca live?

If she were found alive, he would endanger himself and lose the foundation of trust that the emperor had built up in the Vollachian Empire.

As Emperor of Vollachia, any argument could justify it.

It can't be done. Of course not. That was not a rationally given command.

It was an emotional desire, a wish,a prayer.

Vincent Abellux didn't want to kill his beloved sister.

So Prisca Benedict was kept alive and Vincent wore the false crown.

That made Chisha happy.

It wasn't that Prisca had been saved, but that Vincent wanted to keep Prisca alive, and asked Chisha for a way to get rid of the obstacle――the wheel stuck in the ditch.

Chisha: [Was that foreshadowing?]

The nonsense Cecilus uttered before the “Imperial Election Ceremony” began crossed his mind.

Even if it doesn't make sense at the moment and seems meaningless, later on some meaning can be found in it. It can be understood as having been there for that purpose.

The position and actions of himself and Chisha may be the foundation for such a future.

Chisha: [Well, it's really annoying to admit that Cecilus hit the mark, and I can see him getting carried away, so I won't ever tell him.]

Vincent: [It's been like this for a while, but lately I've been thinking a lot. Have you completely lost your hair color and everything you cultivated by serving this Emperor?]

Chisha: [Surprisingly, I've been doing well since wandering the abyss of death.]

Knowing it was disrespectful, Chisha shrugged in front of Vincent. The emperor, who has changed his position, won't blame him unless he does it in front of the public.

Vincent called himself “Emperor”, and the reflection of Chisha in his black eyes was, as he pointed out, completely white with no color.

During the "Imperial Selection Ceremony," Chisha's black hair had lost all of its color and turned completely white when he returned from the brink of death after being nearly killed by an enemy he had confronted.

Since then, he has been wearing white, which is the opposite of the black costumes he had been wearing for some reason. He has even repainted his favorite iron fan, and has thoroughly dressed his entire body in white.

Of course, it wasn't just for fun.

After wandering in the abyss of death and losing his hair color, Chisha developed a strange “Ability”. In order to handle this "Ability" that is dyed in the color of others, it is necessary to have a constant awareness.

It was a necessary measure to imply to himself that he would be dyed in any color.

In any case, the details of this "Ability" are hidden from Vincent as well. Of course, he won't reveal it to anyone, not even the loose lipped Cecilus or others with whom he has little connection.

It is always a good idea to have an ace up one's sleeve, a trump card, or a secret move or two ready to go.

However――,

Chisha: [If Your Excellency will finally release me for the great work I have done, then I do not think there is any need for such intrigue.]

Vincent: [Suppose if you were me, do you think I would let you go through the night in peace, knowing the most important fact that this empire must keep secret, and leave you alive?]

Chisha: [It's somewhat bad manners to develop a hypothetical story into a hypothetical story, but I think the end will be for this head to fall before it leaves the castle.]

