Vincent said this in an arrogant way while resting his chin in his hands on his desk.

It's hard to say if both of them are serious, but it's necessary for the emperor, who doesn't have enough words for others, to let him speak out like this and confirm it.

According to this, apparently Chisha Gold's position and required role will remain the same whether Vincent became emperor or not, but――,

Chisha: [――The state of the Sacred Vollachian Empire may or may not change.]

Already, the brilliant “Yang Sword”, the absolute symbol of the Vollachian Empire, has been betrayed.

Since the "Imperial Election ceremony" that has continued since the founding of the nation has ended in a different form than before, what will follow will also change dramatically in the future.

Going down that path is Vincent, who prioritized his own desires and chose to save his sister.

A new path will be opened up that is different from the one of the past. Chisha found himself slightly excited by that fact and the anticipation.

However, he never showed it in his expression, words, or attitude.

Because he was aware of the bad influence of his friend, Cecilus.

