――The days passed by at a dizzying pace.

The former system of the "Nine Divine Generals" was restored, and the rankings of the Imperial Nobility were reset.

Purging those who had lost their meaning and enjoyed high status because of history alone, the way of the Vollachian Empire which flew the national flag of a “wolf pierced by swords” was enforced at home and abroad without exception.

The way of doing things that had lasted till the previous Emperor, who unthinkingly believed the unwritten rule that the strong were absolutely right and let the Empire fall to ruin internally, was completely disavowed and the initial principle that the strong were respected was scrubbed out.

Those rested on their bloodlines and family’s social standing were robbed of what represented them, while those who had been waiting vigilantly for the opportunity to come around were given a chance to take on the challenge.

From the outside, Vincent Vollachia's reign might have seemed no different from the history of the Empire so far.

However, the reality was quite different. Those who knew what was going on behind the scenes experienced it firsthand.

Before long, it became something that many in the Empire, and even those outside in other countries, would likely know.

The grandeur of Vincent Vollachia's remaking and reforming of the Empire.

Useless conflicts would cease, and absurd deathmatches would no longer be applauded.

Proof of strength was no longer based on an individual's military prowess, and those who held ambitions not suitable for their stature would prove the difficulty of truly fulfilling those ambitions with their lives.

It was as if they were watching the process of completely changing the basis for what was “strong.”

However――,

???: [I'll be "First", Anya will be "Second", and after Olbart joins Chisha will be "Fourth". Your Excellency's choices aren’t so bad, but Chisha's complexion isn’t great, is it?]

