Cecilus: [His Excellency, or someone else, can fulfill their purpose. My one greatest flaw as the leading actor of this world, is that there’s only one of me in this world.]

There were those whose natures would not change at all, even if they gained standing or the way of the Empire changed.

However, Cecilus embodied that first principle, the reason for why, in the oldest eras of the Vollachian Empire, “the strong” garnered respect from everyone.

Everyone throughout the Empire knew the person in question was unpopular, did not have a personality that would be liked by everyone, and did not have the character to be an example for anyone.

Still, should anyone be asked who the strongest in the Empire was, their chests swelled with pride as if they were tied to it personally.

It was Cecilus Segmunt that was the most powerful being in the Empire.

The fact that Chisha was considered to be able to take a thousand seconds by gathering people against Cecilus had also been the reason why he settled without firmly refusing the position of “Fourth” of the Nine Divine Generals.

Hence, even while thinking it was overvalued, Chisha had resigned himself to that position and role. For the most part, it worked well.

